main event: A bright white spherical object was observed for over 4 hours in Thurston-Pierce counties, Washington.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 4 hours and 11 minutes., The object was very bright and appeared to be spherical., The sighting coincided with the position of Venus, which was very bright in the early dawn., The observation was made by a civilian source., The documented altitude and azimuth provided detailed tracking of the object.
